<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870313-0130 </DOCNO><HL> General Dynamics UnitGets a Navy ContractTotaling $44.7 Million</HL><DD> 03/13/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GD MTI TXT UTX HONDEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The electric boat division of General Dynamics Corp. won a $44.7 million Navy contract to develop the steam and electric plant for the Seawolf attack submarine.    Hazeltine Corp. received a $33.5 million Navy contract for sonobuoy communications equipment for P-3 and S-3 aircraft.    Morton Thiokol Inc. was awarded a $17.5 million Navy contract for rocket motors for high-speed missiles.    Bell Helicopter Textron, a unit of Textron Inc., was issued a $15.6 million Navy contract for AH-1T helicopter improvements.    Pratt andamp; Whitney, a unit of United Technologies Corp., got a $14.7 million Navy contract for J-52 aircraft engines.    Honeywell Inc. received a $12 million Navy contract for MH-53E helicopter-training equipment. </TEXT></DOC>